content: Carmen Chui (she/her) is currently a Senior Business Data Architect at the Bank of Nova Scotia (Scotiabank) in Toronto, Canada. Her research interests include ontology engineering, knowledge representation and modelling, and their applications. She has worked on projects to develop and analyze ontologies in science (manufacturing, geometry, chemistry) and anthropology (kinship).
